<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">
Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Risbec" box="[312,470,223,248]" pageId="33" pageNumber="114" refString="Risbec, J. (1952) Contribution a l'etude des chalcidoides de Madagascar. Memoires de l'Institut Scientifique de Madagascar, Serie E, 2, 1 - 449." type="journal article" year="1952">Risbec (1952)</bibRefCitation>
did not state the number of specimens or the collecting date (other descriptions in the same paper do mention these), he gave a single body length. This indicates a single specimen and I therefore interpret the 
<typeStatus box="[294,342,296,320]" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">type</typeStatus>
in 
<collectionCode box="[379,464,296,319]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">MNHN</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation box="[479,636,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 – 123" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1434,1197,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[168,1453,1197,1939]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 120 – 123. Reikosiella (Hirticauda) bekilyi (Risbec) (holotype): 120, head and mesosoma, dorsal; 121, fore wing; 122, face; 123; middle leg, tibial apex and tarsus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256065/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Figs 120–123</figureCitation>
) as the 
<typeStatus box="[723,825,295,320]" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">holotype</typeStatus>
. It is contorted, mounted by a minutien pin through its mesosoma between the mesonotum and acropleuron at the base of the metanotum, and lacks it gaster, right antenna beyond fl2, left antenna beyond fl1 (
<figureCitation box="[560,657,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 – 123" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1434,1197,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[168,1453,1197,1939]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 120 – 123. Reikosiella (Hirticauda) bekilyi (Risbec) (holotype): 120, head and mesosoma, dorsal; 121, fore wing; 122, face; 123; middle leg, tibial apex and tarsus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256065/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Fig. 122</figureCitation>
), and right hind leg beyond the coxa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,1705,1757]" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,240,1705,1726]" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">MAP 1.</emphasis>
