</taxonomicName>
species (number given in any country indicates number of site records represented by closely set symbols).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="115" pageId="33" pageNumber="114" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1802,2007]" lastBlockId="34.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="115" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1802,1827]" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Remarks</emphasis>
. Although its gaster is missing, the 
<typeStatus box="[737,835,1802,1827]" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[880,1131,1802,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Macreupelmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bekilyi">
<emphasis box="[880,1131,1802,1826]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Macreupelmus bekilyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is assigned to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yoshimoto" authorityName="Yoshimoto" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Reikosiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1311,1435,1802,1826]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Reikosiella</emphasis>
Yoshimoto
</taxonomicName>
based on, among other features, the lack of a mesotibial apical groove (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1196,1838,1863]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 – 123" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1434,1197,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[168,1453,1197,1939]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 120 – 123. Reikosiella (Hirticauda) bekilyi (Risbec) (holotype): 120, head and mesosoma, dorsal; 121, fore wing; 122, face; 123; middle leg, tibial apex and tarsus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256065/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Fig. 123</figureCitation>
), comparatively long fore wing marginal vein (
<figureCitation box="[454,555,1874,1899]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 – 123" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1434,1197,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[168,1453,1197,1939]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 120 – 123. Reikosiella (Hirticauda) bekilyi (Risbec) (holotype): 120, head and mesosoma, dorsal; 121, fore wing; 122, face; 123; middle leg, tibial apex and tarsus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256065/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Fig. 121</figureCitation>
), ∩-like scrobal depression that extends to the inner orbits (
<figureCitation box="[1269,1371,1874,1899]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 – 123" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1434,1197,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[168,1453,1197,1939]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 120 – 123. Reikosiella (Hirticauda) bekilyi (Risbec) (holotype): 120, head and mesosoma, dorsal; 121, fore wing; 122, face; 123; middle leg, tibial apex and tarsus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256065/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Fig. 122</figureCitation>
), and subbasally compressed scape. Further, it is a member of 
<taxonomicName box="[786,911,1910,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Reikosiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[786,911,1910,1934]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Reikosiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Boucek" authorityName="Boucek" box="[927,1144,1910,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Hirticauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[927,1050,1910,1934]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Hirticauda</emphasis>
Bouček
</taxonomicName>
) based on the presence of a row of mesotibial apical pegs (
<figureCitation box="[538,639,1946,1971]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 – 123" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1434,1197,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[168,1453,1197,1939]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 120 – 123. Reikosiella (Hirticauda) bekilyi (Risbec) (holotype): 120, head and mesosoma, dorsal; 121, fore wing; 122, face; 123; middle leg, tibial apex and tarsus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256065/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="114">Fig. 123</figureCitation>
), dorsellum apically recurved, cup-like, over apex of scutellum, and acropleural sulcus posteriorly sinuately curved so that a slender mesepisternum is differentiated between the acropleuron and mesocoxa (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Gibson" box="[516,665,151,176]" pageId="34" pageNumber="115" refString="Gibson, G. A. P. (1995) Parasitic wasps of the subfamily Eupelminae: classification and revision of world genera (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea: Eupelmidae). Memoirs on Entomology, International, 5, i - v + 1 - 421." type="journal article" year="1995">Gibson 1995</bibRefCitation>
). Based on these features I hereby transfer 
<taxonomicName box="[1157,1406,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Macreupelmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bekilyi">
<emphasis box="[1157,1406,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="115">Macreupelmus bekilyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[151,275,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Reikosiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,275,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="115">Reikosiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="Risbec" authorityName="Risbec" box="[316,678,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Macreupelmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bekilyi" status="n. comb." subGenus="Hirticauda">
<emphasis box="[316,333,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="115">R</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[359,482,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="115">Hirticauda</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[500,575,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="115">bekilyi</emphasis>
(Risbec)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[687,791,188,213]" pageId="34" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[687,791,188,213]" pageId="34" pageNumber="115">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
According to the original description the antennae were entirely dark, without some white funiculars, unlike many species of the subgenus from the region. The fore wing is bifasciate (
<figureCitation box="[299,397,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 120 – 123" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[168,1434,1197,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[168,1453,1197,1939]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 120 – 123. Reikosiella (Hirticauda) bekilyi (Risbec) (holotype): 120, head and mesosoma, dorsal; 121, fore wing; 122, face; 123; middle leg, tibial apex and tarsus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256065/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="115">Fig. 121</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
